President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Heidi R. King of California as the Administrator of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA), Department of Transportation. Ms. King is currently the Deputy Administrator of the NHTSA and has a strong background in economics and regulatory policy. She has previously served as the Chief Economist for the House Committee on Energy and Commerce during the 112th Congress and has also worked in the White House's Office of Management and Budget. Additionally, Ms. King has experience in traffic safety and emergency response, having served as a California State Park Ranger and a volunteer Emergency Medical Technician.